Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: Warm Up100m freestyle (fins optional) [Posture] 4x50 Free as 25 Poor posture / 25 Tall and Proud Posture 0:15 SR Feel the difference in strength and power between good vs bad posture [Head position] 100 Free as 25 Looking Down / 25 Looking Forwards / 25 Looking at 45 degrees / 25 Experiment To Find Your Ideal Head Position [Kick] 2x25 Of Knee Into Hip Kick (See video below) - Fins Optional 150 Free -Put all three together (posture, head position and kick) Total: 600m -------------------------------------------- Workout #1 3x100 at 60/70/80% effort 0:30 secs rest - Focus on 'tall and proud' posture 3x100 at 60/70/80% effort 0:30 secs rest - Focus on correct head position with top of head just above surface 3x100 at 60/70/80% effort 0:30 secs rest - Focus on keeping the kick effort easy and small kicks (think of the bucket) 100 Easy swim down *For the sets of 3x100's above, it means the first 100 is at 60%, the next one at 70% and the final 100 is at 80% effort. Total: 1km

Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: 100m freestyle (fins optional) [Balance] 2x50 as 25 Body Position Kick / 25 Swim 0:15 SR (fins and snorkel) In the drill aim to get your shoulder, back and hips as high in the water as possible. 2x50 as 25 Front Kick / 25 Swim 0:15 SR (fins and snorkel) This drill is similar to 'body position kick' but now aim to keep your head, hips and heels near the surface so you're in a horizontal body position [Alignment & Hand Position] 2x50 as 25 Front Kick / 25 Swim 0:15 SR (fins and snorkel) During front kick drill keep two things in mind. Train tracks (keep hand in line with shoulders) and starting catch position (make sure you fingers are the same depth as your armpit). When you go into the swim after the drill, keep those two things in mind. 4x50 Free - Focus on train tracks, start of catch and keeping your head, hips and heels at the surface Total: 600m 12x50 Freestyle @ 60% effort 0:15 SR - Focus on keeping head, hips and heels near surface by leaning on chest, bracing core, and squeezing butt cheeks 8x50 Freestyle @ 70% effort 0:30 SR - Same focus as above 4x50 Freestyle @ 80% effort 0:45 SR - Same focus as above Total: 1.2km

Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: 100m freestyle (fins optional) 4x50 of 25 6-1-6 drill / 25 swim (Fins and snorkel) - Make sure your shoulder is out of the water while you're kicking on the side, bring your arm over feeling as though your elbow is leading the way, enter fingers first. 4x50 of 25 Wide Fingertip drag drill / 25 swim (Fins) - Relax your hand so you can drag your fingers on the surface and feel your elbow lead the arm over the water 2x50 of Entry Drill with Kickboard (Fins) - Swap arms on the second 50. This drill helps you enter fingers first because the kickboard ensures you don't over-reach Total: 600m Workout #1 As you change your speed in the set, aim to keep your recovery relaxed and entering with your fingers first 4x50 Free with 0:30 SR - (Build 1-4 so #4 is the fastest) 4x100 Free with 0:45 SR - (Build 1-4 so #4 is the fastest) 4x150 Free with 0:60 SR - (Build 1-4 so #4 is the fastest) Total: 1.2km

Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: 200m Easy Freestyle (with fins) 6x50 of 25 Slow Doggy Scoop / 25 Freestyle 0:20 secs rest 2x100 of 25 Single Arm Scoop (Left) / 25 Single Arm Scoop (Right) / 50 Freestyle 0:20 secs rest 4x50 Freestyle (with pull buoy) - This will help you concentrate on the catch and feel the water on your hand and forearm Total: 900m Workout #1 Focus on your catch in this set and start very easy with the 60% effort, so you can increase your pace throughout the set. 6x100 Freestyle @60% w/ 0:20 SR 4x100 Freestyle @70% w/ 0:30 SR 2x100 Freestyle @80% w/ 0:40 SR 100 easy recovery Total: 1.3km

Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: 200m Easy Freestyle (with fins) 6x50 of 25 Slow Doggy Scoop / 25 Freestyle 0:20 secs rest 2x100 of 25 Single Arm Scoop (Left) / 25 Single Arm Scoop (Right) / 50 Freestyle 0:20 secs rest 4x50 Freestyle (with pull buoy) - This will help you concentrate on the catch and feel the water on your hand and forearm Total: 900m Workout #2 20x50 freestyle w/ :20 SR as: Odd - Minimum Stroke Count* Even - Build (start easy, finish fast) 4x150 Pull @70% w/ 0:30 SR *Try to hold the minimum amount of strokes for each lap. The way to reduce your stroke count is to improve your catch, so try to reduce your stroke count by focusing on your catch Total: 1.6km

Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: 200m Easy Freestyle (with fins) 6x50 of 25 Slow Doggy Scoop / 25 Freestyle 0:20 secs rest 2x100 of 25 Single Arm Scoop (Left) / 25 Single Arm Scoop (Right) / 50 Freestyle 0:20 secs rest 4x50 Freestyle (with pull buoy) - This will help you concentrate on the catch and feel the water on your hand and forearm Total: 900m Workout #3 2x Sets of: 200 @ 70% effort w/ 0:20 SR 50 @ 90% effort w/ 0:30 SR 150 @ 70% effort w/ 0:20 SR 50 @ 90% effort w/ 0:30 SR 100 @ 70% effort w/ 0:20 SR 50 @ 90% effort w/ 0:30 SR 50 @ 70% effort w/ 0:20 SR 50 @ 90% effort w/ 0:30 SR Total: 1.4km

Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: Use fins and snorkel for entire warm up 200m freestyle (with fins) 2x50 of 25 Doggy Scoop / 25 Swim This will help refresh the high elbow catch movement 2x50 of 25 Power Diamond / 25 Swim Keep elbows wide, and shoulders and back relaxed 4x50 of 25 YMCA drill / 25 swim Take your time to make sure you get each of the 4 positions 100% correct, because when you do this it will help change your technique when you move into the full freestyle stroke 4x50 Freestyle 0:30 secs rest Feel yourself moving through the catch and power diamond as you swim. Remember to keep relaxed and keep your normal rhythm and timing, don't over-think it and become stiff and mechanical in your movements Total: 800m Workout #1 Because you're gradually increasing your speed in this set, you can focus on your catch and power diamond and aim to maintain it as you get quicker. 3x200 Freestyle @ 60/70/80% w/ 0:40 SR 4x100 Freestyle @60/70/80/90% w/ 0:30 SR 4x50 Freestyle @ 60/70/80/90% w/ 0:30 SR 100 easy recovery Total: 1.3km

Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: Use fins and snorkel for entire warm up 200m freestyle (with fins) 4x50 of Fiddle Faddle Drill Swap paddle and fins to the other side after 2x50's. Feel for the cross-connection across the body 4x50 of 25 Single Arm (Kick Timing) Drill / 25 Swim Take a lot of time during the reach phase of the stroke so you can lengthen through your upper body and arm to help with the serape effect. Focus on kicking at the correc time on each leg 4x50 freestyle (focused on catch and kick going together on the same side) Total: 800m Workout #1 This set is focused solely on keeping the kick and catch timing as you increase in speed. 30x50 Build 1-3 (60/70/80%) w/ 0:20 SR 100 easy recovery Total: 1.6km

Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: 200m freestyle (with fins) 4x50 of 25 Straight Arm Recovery Freestyle / 25 Swim 4x50 of 15 overspeed / 35 easy freestyle - Overspeed means move your arms as quick as possible and intentionally 'spin the wheels'. This helps you feel comfortable for when you go to increase your stroke rate. Total: 600m Workout #1 7 x 100 Freestyle with 0:30 secs rest – Using a FINIS tempo trainer, increase your stroke rate by 4 each 100 (Use the guide below to choose your stroke rate for the first 100) – Record time, stroke rate, stroke count and perceived effort If your race pace is 1:30 or faster start at 56spm If your race pace is 1:31-2:00 start at 52spm If your race pace is 2:01 or greater start at 48spm Total: 700m

Title: Aerobic Swim
WorkoutDescription: 200m freestyle (with fins) 4x50 of 25 Straight Arm Recovery Freestyle / 25 Swim 4x50 of 15 overspeed / 35 easy freestyle - Overspeed means move your arms as quick as possible and intentionally 'spin the wheels'. Total: 600m Workout #2 The 100's with 25 fast in the beginning are designed to get your stroke rate up, so that in the 70 and 90% effort 100's, you feel like a faster stroke rate is easier to hold. 3 sets of: 5x100 with 0:30 SR as: 100 as 25 fast / 75 easy 100 @ 70% 100 as 25 fast / 75 easy 100 @ 90% 100 easy recovery 100 swim down easy Total: 1.6km

Title: Aerobic Swim

Title: Peak Phase 2: Strength and Conditioning #1
WorkoutDescription: Please check the link below for full exercise instructions, progressions, alternatives and videos: https://www.myprocoach.net/wp-content/uploads/SC-Triathlon.pdf Whole Body Strength: 1. Squat: 3 x 8 (Exercise 1) 2. Alternate Lunge: 3 x 9 (Exercise 5) 3. Calf Raise: 3 x 10 (Exercise 8) 4. Lat & Front Raise Combo: 3 x 7 (Exercise 11) 5. Dumbbell Pullover: 2 x 12 (Exercise 15) 6: Glute Bridge: 3 x 12 (Exercise 18) 7. Bicycle Crunch: 3 x 10 (Exercise 26) 8. Plank: 3 reps (Exercise 21) 9. Sit-Up: 2 x 12 (Exercise 27) Flexibility: 10-15 minutes Notes: 1. 3 x 8 = 3 sets of 8 repetitions with a rest between sets. 2. Rests are 30 - 50 secs. 3. When an exercise alternates right and left, the right PLUS left movement is 1 rep. 4. For unilateral exercises, perform reps on the right, then repeat on the left. Then move to next set. 5. Breathe out on exertion and maintain form throughout. 6. For flexibility see the link below or choose stretches that work well for you.
CoachComments: Peak Phase: This phase allows you to focus on sport-specific training. This means decreasing the stress of your strength and conditioning training session by reducing intensity and volume. The time allowed for flexibility is increased, maintaining mobility and range of movement during this phase is key. Resistance during the Peak Phase: The resistance should reduce back to what you were lifting in the Base Phase. Stay focused on form. Perform strength and conditioning once each week for this phase. Avoid the ‘no pain, no gain’ thinking. Strength will compliment your training making you more powerful, less prone to injury and help you focus on range of movement required for all three disciplines. It should not inhibit your subsequent workouts.
